crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: APP-DETECT Apple Messages push.apple.com DNS TXT request attempt
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert udp $HOME_NET any -> any 53 ( msg:"APP-DETECT Apple Messages push.apple.com DNS TXT request attempt"; flow:to_server; byte_test:1,!&,0xF8,2; content:"|04|push|05|apple|03|com|00 00 10 00 01|",fast_pattern,nocase; metadata:policy max-detect-ips drop; service:dns; reference:url,www.apple.com/osx/apps/all.html#messages; classtype:policy-violation; sid:25080; rev:2; )

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The script first executes the `query session` command, redirecting its output to a file named "session.txt". It then iterates through the lines of "session.txt", skipping the first line. For each remaining line, it extracts the third token (separated by spaces or tabs). The extracted token is then used as an argument to the `logoff` command. Finally, the script deletes the "session.txt" file. The overall effect is to log off user sessions based on information retrieved by the query session command.
